'''The FEATURES variable contains a list of Portage features that the user wants enabled on his system, effectively setting Portage behavior.'''

The FEATURES variable is by default already set by the users' profile, but can be updated through /etc/make.conf.

For more information, please see [http://www.gentoo.org/doc/en/handbook/handbook-x86.xml?part=2&chap=3 Portage Features] in the Gentoo Handbook.

